{"key":"post-7853058","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7853058</id>\n<content>In front of a laminar flow hood, or inside a glovebox, simply shave a small piece of tissue from the inside of the stem and place on agar.  Within 24 to 48 hours, you'll have a culture.  If there's any contaminants, you'll easily see them on the petri dish, and can transfer healthy mycelium away from it to a fresh dish.  When the culture is pure, transfer to grains.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7853093</next>\n<prev>7853054</prev>\n<first>7852457</first>\n<last>7853099</last>\n<when>1199901474</when>\n<utime>01/09/08 07:57 PM</utime>\n</post>"}